A PNP model for the 2023 game pieces is not currently supported (and we do not plan to) for a multitude of reasons dealing with the actual technical implementations.

Perspective-n-Point [1] (the algorithm used for getting the 3D values) is the problem of estimating the pose of a calibrated camera given a set of n 3D points in the world and their corresponding 2D projections in the image. (Wikipedia)

Getting these points in both dimensions are non trivial given how many orientations the game piece can be at, which angle you’re viewing it at, etc. AprilTags on the other hand you just always have 4 corners in very known positions so its easy.

At least that is my take on the problem, others may have a different interpretation.
